# Contact form email delivery (Resend — https://resend.com)
#
# When a visitor submits the contact form, it is emailed to your support inbox
# using a Resend template. No email is sent to the visitor.
#
# Setup:
#   1. Sign up / log in at resend.com and create an API key
#      (https://resend.com/api-keys) → RESEND_API_KEY.
#   2. Verify your sending domain at https://resend.com/domains, then set
#      CONTACT_FROM_EMAIL to an address on it, e.g. "FIDE <noreply@fidelabs.io>".
#   3. Create a template: Resend dashboard → Templates → Create. Paste the HTML
#      from email-templates/contact-notification.html, set the subject to
#      "New contact message from {{fullName}}", save, and copy the template ID
#      → CONTACT_TEMPLATE_ID.
#   4. Set CONTACT_TO_EMAIL to the inbox that should receive submissions.
#
# All four values are required for the form to send.

RESEND_API_KEY=
CONTACT_TEMPLATE_ID=
CONTACT_TO_EMAIL=
CONTACT_FROM_EMAIL=
